                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d42">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.90H/67½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from"
                            >Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-16">March 16,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Why not name the regular Minister to Afghanistan now and get it over with?
                    Perhaps you can find someone from a demobilized Embassy or Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                            >oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
